ðŸŸ  Apache Web Server on Ubuntu EC2

Today, I explored how to install, configure, and manage the Apache Web Server on an Ubuntu EC2 instance. This is essential for hosting static websites and learning how servers serve web content on the cloud.

ðŸ”§ Steps to install and configure Apache on Ubuntu:
Install Apache

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install apache2 -y
Control Apache service

sudo service apache2 start      # Start the server
sudo service apache2 status     # Check server status
sudo service apache2 reload     # Reload configuration
sudo service apache2 stop       # Stop the server
Default HTML directory


cd /var/www/html/
Edit Apache config file

sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf
